    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9216" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπο-δέχομαι</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑποδέξομαι</span>, aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπεδέξατο</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπέδεξο,
            -έδεκτο</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑποδέχθαι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑποδέγμενος</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">receive</span>, esp. of friendly, hospitable welcome,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πρόφρων, οἴκῳ</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.70</span></i>; also with a thing as subject,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κοῖτος, πῆμα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 14.275</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            βίᾱς</span>, receive silently, submit to, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">endure</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 13.310</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">undertake,
            promise</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.93</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.387</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
